South Africa Allocates Smallest Amount of Inflation-Linked Bonds This Year

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-03-25T09:51:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-25/south-africa-allocates-smallest-amount-of-inflation-linked-bonds-this-year.html
South Africa  sold the smallest
amount of inflation-linked bonds this year at today’s auction,
the third weekly sale at which the amount allocated was below
that offered this year.  Africa’s biggest economy sold 360 million rand of
inflation-linked debt maturing in 2028, 2022 and 2033, having
offered 600 million rand of the securities at the sale, the
Pretoria-based central bank said on its Bloomberg page.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  